{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 207242, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "sebag2", "body": "posted here macros really help,\nnot a hard boss if you have a druid healer.\ndid it today (26.12) with fury war/prot war/rogue/lock/me(resto drood)\n\njust heal all, use macros, insygnia when u get stunned and its critical. same with the mana bomb. just wait and do some rejuv + swiftmend when it get's ugly.\n\ndid it with pug group of tottal retards and tank with green shit.", "date": "2007-12-25T19:24:47-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2007-12-25T19:26:13-06:00", 1, "sebag2"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 212732, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "cechjakpoleno", "body": "I wrote another macro for targeting and HoTing spirits\nWith this you can have only one macro instead of 3 for each spirit, with click of mouse 1 button, you'll HoT Hawk spirit, with mouse 2 (note that mouse 2 is right button, not midle) Falcon, and mouse 3 (midle) will target and HoT Eagle\n\n[code]/target [button:1] Hawk Spirit\n/target [button:3] Eagle Spirit\n/target [button:2] Falcon Spirit\n/cast Rejuvenation(Rank 1)\n/targetlasttarget\n[/code]\nRemember that you can replace Rejuvenation(Rank 1) with Regrowth(rank1), if you prefer 2sec cast and 21s Hot instead of instant  cast with 8s HoT\n\nMacro will after HoTing spirit retarget to your last target. (iIf you are tank, It will HoT spirit without deselecting Anzu)\n\n*Ranks 1 is used to save mana\n**Sorry for my english :)", "date": "2008-01-04T10:32:58-06:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-01-04T16:42:21-06:00", 2, "cechjakpoleno"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 222060, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "73758", "body": "I noticed that in a previous comment that they said the Essence Infused Moonstone was consumed each time.  This is no longer the case and so long as after you complete your quest, go back to the quest giver.  He will give you a new one that can be reused over and over again.", "date": "2008-01-22T01:22:47-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 257633, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "haloman800", "body": "The possible drop for the mount isent common... the only reason its on the front row is because this boss dosent drop any trash items, the drop rate is 0.8% or 23 out of 2860 if it hasent changed lately - Golgothaa of Anentheron, one lucky gnome who got the mount.\r\n\r\nEDIT: this mount looks exacly like Anzu the Raven Lord himself", "date": "2008-03-22T18:00:39-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-03-22T18:03:20-05:00", 1, "haloman800"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 262227, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Erlinn", "body": "A fairly \"simple\" yet quite fun fight. I just down him as a feral tank in moderate gear with a warrior, hunter, and mage dpsing and a priest healing. We wiped once, but only because of bad luck; Anzu cast his Cyclone quite often, but it just so happened to land on the priest EVERY time he did it. Afterwards, we downed him with little difficulty.\n\nThis quest is the \"tree of life stage\" of this quest and is MUCH easier with a druid healing or dpsing rather than tanking. But fortunately, when Anzu banishes, it gives you time to cast some rank 1 Regrowths and Rejuvs on the birds. I suggest going for the eagle first, as the bird spawns will be the most pressing issue at the time, then the other two. Since it's only rank one, you can easily spam them. Right before Anzu unbanishes (when all the birds are dead) top off each bird with a fresh regrowth (it lasts the longest) and quickly jump into bear form. It's a simple tank and spank aside for that.", "date": "2008-03-28T22:10:36-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-03-28T22:11:34-05:00", 1, "Erlinn"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 282895, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "149345", "body": "You don't need backup healers or a dedicated healing druid for the stones.\r\n\r\nI tank him and when he spawns birds I let the DPS handle it and rejuvenate the statues, that is enough of a help, you don't need the statues up 24/7", "date": "2008-05-05T13:59:27-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 285066, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Uttermadnez", "body": "Guys consider this...the Eagle statue (click and read) http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=40240 appears to have two methods of working:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]using rejuvenation or regrowth will make the statue attack the boss once every 3 seconds.[/li]\r\n[/ul][ul]\r\n[li]using lifebloom appears to make the statue attack once every 1 second.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\nso my theory is for someone to test regrowthing the hawk and falcon, while keeping lifebloom on the eagle to triple its damage to the boss.\r\n\r\nsomeone please try to confirm this.", "date": "2008-05-09T09:41:55-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 290006, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "146485", "body": "What is the 'key' that goes into your keyring after you finish the quest? I don't see it on my keyring...", "date": "2008-05-17T17:27:07-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 295669, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "152007", "body": "This boss isnt as hard as you all make him sound. I just ran it yesterday with crap CC. The whole \"journey\" getting there was rough but the boss fight was a complete cake walk. War tank, feral drood, 2 resto droods, and mage. Yea..was a late night and server reset so no one was on...It went alright, couldve been better with more CC but this boss is way too easy. All you really need to watch out for is the spellbomb and just keep the bird spirits up.\n\n@scyther \"What is the 'key' that goes into your keyring after you finish the quest? I don't see it on my keyring...\"\nYou get it after you turn in the quest. Its a follow up after killing Anzu back at Cenarion Refuge.", "date": "2008-05-27T17:03:33-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-05-27T17:04:33-05:00", 1, "152007"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 353850, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "140506", "body": "i just did it today, i was fairly easy.\r\ngroup: 2 locks, 1 Pala (healer), 1 Shaman (enh), Druid (feral) <-- me\r\ni was walk-in-the-park fight. i managed to activate the birds' statues when Anzu is banished", "date": "2008-08-15T16:08:01-05:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 371460, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "16215", "body": "Here are some helpful macros that will put rejuvenation on the spirits without you even noticing you switched targets :-)\r\n\r\n[s][b]Macro1[/b][/s]\r\n/target Hawk Spirit\r\n/cast Rejuvenation(Rank 1)\r\n/target Anzu\r\n\r\n[s][b]Macro2[/b][/s]\r\n/target Eagle Spirit\r\n/cast Rejuvenation(Rank 1)\r\n/target Anzu\r\n\r\n[s][b]Macro3[/b][/s]\r\n/target Falcon Spirit\r\n/cast Rejuvenation(Rank 1)\r\n/target Anzu\r\n\r\n\r\nWhenever I clicked a macro, it worked so fast I LITERALLY couldn't tell it switched targets--but it works, just click these all 3 times and voila.\r\n\r\n(Also you can switch the rejuvenation rank1 with any other HoT--just make sure it's rank one, and that it'll stay on for at least 10 seconds (you don't need longer than 10 seconds, but it's useless to just sit there and constantly be re-applying the buffs))\r\n\r\nThe issue with the macros posted above is that your last target may not have been anzu.\r\nYou can also switch Anzu with a tanks name--if you're a healer, or etc. etc.\r\n\r\nI hope this helped :)", "date": "2008-09-08T03:46:42-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 423071, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "89170", "body": "This boss may be getting removed, as Swift Flight Form will be Trainable in patch 3.0.3", "date": "2008-10-28T10:53:36-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As far as i know it won't be removed, Swift flight form will be trainable at 71, but you will still be able to complete the quest for it at 70.", "creationdate": "2008-11-05T13:48:47-06:00", "id": 54509, "rating": 9, "commentid": 423071, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "jhtocca", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 426692, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "gerwim", "body": "As a note: In 3.0.2 it doesn't matter which rank you will use, since every rank costs the same amount of mana.", "date": "2008-10-31T16:29:58-05:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Lower ranks actually cost MORE mana... the top rank of lifebloom costs my druid 628, rank 1 costs 900something.", "creationdate": "2009-05-01T10:12:08-05:00", "id": 403363, "rating": 3, "commentid": 426692, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Azaram", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 456937, "nreplies": 12, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hurono", "body": "I hate to ask, but is this boss even still available? Patch 3.2 doesn't give any other Druid Quests to reach new forms (that I am aware of), and if these don't exist anymore, then this boss can't be fought. I want to be sure, because once I hit 70, I want to get the Reins he drops lol. Please, someone answer?", "date": "2008-11-19T20:24:43-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed he's still available.  He's easily soloable as a feral druid (some Naxx 25 gear, mostly heroic epics), so I've been going in once a day this week.  3 runs no mount, but I'm glad to see someone else got one and can confirm it still drops.  Feral druids, stealth all the way to his room, clear the Ravenguards and the 6 pulls inside the run, then summon him.  Beat him down to 66% and heal yourself while you wait for the birds to come down.  Swipe the birds, heal again and repeat.  Barkskin during peirching screach and that's it.  Someone said you can solo him as a balance druid, but I'm ", "creationdate": "2008-11-19T20:24:44-06:00", "id": 370233, "rating": 7, "commentid": 456937, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "emorphous", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This boss is still summonable in WotLK; he's pretty easy to solo as a feral druid tank, but I haven't seen the mount drop yet.  Update: I got http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32768 today, so the mount definitely still drops. Woo hoo!", "creationdate": "2008-11-27T22:29:25-06:00", "id": 59930, "rating": 15, "commentid": 456937, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "zadiel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just soloed him as a lvl 80 feral (bear spec) druid. He's pretty easy, just make sure you heal quickly to full, before all the birds jump you, every time he banishes.  My rough stats in bear are 32k health, 32k armor, 34.2% dodge, 4.4k attack power and around 30% crit.", "creationdate": "2008-12-05T07:02:29-06:00", "id": 62091, "rating": 7, "commentid": 456937, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "triglav", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "For the record, I prowled past the trash and the first boss easily while specced 0 feral talents.  Feral Instinct is not needed.  Unfortunately, I found quickly that boomkin isn't really the spec to solo Anzu :P", "creationdate": "2009-07-03T22:08:36-05:00", "id": 107582, "rating": 9, "commentid": 456937, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "iamzombie", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Mobs that see stealth sometimes have a bigger stealth aggro radius on high level players than their non-stealth aggro radius.   I can confirm that it is possible to get by the first boss by dropping stealth once you enter the room and wall hugging.", "creationdate": "2010-01-24T22:20:18-06:00", "id": 439764, "rating": 2, "commentid": 456937, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Pinochet", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 497372, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "255459", "body": "The item reward you get from the druid quest implies that he is a goddess, but Anzu's title on this website implies that he is a god. Is it a boy or a girl?", "date": "2008-12-08T07:36:58-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "well if ur a boy or girl it will be ur gender", "creationdate": "2009-01-06T19:19:12-06:00", "id": 378218, "rating": 0, "commentid": 497372, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "297303", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[b]HE[/b] is a God, not a Godess. His title is \"The Raven God\", the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=32449]Essence-Infused Moonstone[/url] says he is a god and the quest chain confirms it.  [quote]Your defeat of Anzu, the raven [i][b]god[/b][/i], is truly a remarkable accomplishment. [b][i]He[/i] [/b]may not abandon his quest to return to Outland, I fear.  As long as [i][b]he[/b][/i] has followers here, [b][i]he[/i][/b] will attempt to rise again. Keep the essence-infused moonstone with you in case we have not heard the last of Anzu.[/quote]", "creationdate": "2009-01-10T16:54:34-06:00", "id": 71798, "rating": 14, "commentid": 497372, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lighter", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Anzu, being the Raven Lord is a male. The Goddess is likely a reference to Elune or the Earth Mother, etc.", "creationdate": "2009-01-28T05:16:52-06:00", "id": 384164, "rating": 0, "commentid": 497372, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "94144", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yes, Anzu is a male. The \"goddess\" refered to in the quest reward is Elune. From your confusion, I think you are probably a Tauren druid, as I think most Night Elves would probably get that right away.", "creationdate": "2009-02-06T16:37:18-06:00", "id": 386521, "rating": 0, "commentid": 497372, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "79104", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Who cares? Either way I plan on mounting it! :D", "creationdate": "2010-09-23T15:55:56-05:00", "id": 183345, "rating": 3, "commentid": 497372, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zhanghia", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-08T07:39:50-06:00", 1, "255459"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 510202, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "cywang86", "body": "Anzu, as with most heroic bosses, is now soloable by an 80 heroic geared tank.\n\nNot sure if it's doable by DPS classes or not as he hits around 1400 on a feral tank.\n\nHealers might have a little trouble due to his spell bomb debuff.\n\nI highly recommend people to try this boss.\n\nBring a druid friend to enjoy the fun if you're not a druid =P", "date": "2008-12-14T19:18:41-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "to cywanq86..   first of all, this is very easily soloed by a well geard druid tank, i stealthed by everything even the first boss, then i cleared all the mobs in that room, i summoned anzu and he was very easily soloed, i never went under 75% health, to tell u the truth, the mobs in the room were harder then the boss himself. so he is very soloable        P.S. u have to bring a druid friend if u r not a druid...who will summon anzu :P", "creationdate": "2009-07-21T10:00:24-05:00", "id": 416560, "rating": 0, "commentid": 510202, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "429200", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-14T19:19:32-06:00", 1, "cywang86"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 516780, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "triglav", "body": "Full naxx 25 feral tank would have above 40% dodge unbuffed...\r\nMy gear when I first time did this was maxed heroic gear with few pieces from naxx 10.\r\n\r\nHere's what I do:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Prowl through trash to the first boss, here I get out of prowl and run by wall around (ironically you have higher chance to pull the boss while in prowl since he has truesight).[/li]\r\n[li]Back to prowl, go upstairs, get into the room with 3 packs of small non-elite birds, 3 other trash packs and one serpent patrol.[/li]\r\n[li]Pull first two birds packs, wait for the serpent patrol and kill it.[/li]\r\n[li]Kill the last pack in front of two ravenguards.[/li]\r\n[li]Kill the ravenguard duo (these mobs are really nasty, make sure you root one before pull, and stun when they enrage).[/li]\r\n[li]Pull the pack inside of the Anzu's room on the right and kill it.[/li]\r\n[li]Pull/kill the serpent patrol in the middle of the room, kill the packs inside the room one by one.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\nI maybe clear more packs that is actually needed, however it's pretty safe this way in case you get feared and can't interrupt it. [b]If you are soloing this and die, you risk the instance reset, which means all the trash respawns[/b].\r\n\r\nFew things about the sethekk packs:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]hibernate those elite birds (swoop is annoying)[/li]\r\n[li]root Talon Lords (they are melee and have stun)[/li]\r\n[li]kill Prophets first (they cast fear, you'll resist many, but be ready to berserk/trinket it in case you get caught in it)[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nBoss \"strategy\":\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]shift to bear and use enrage just when the boss appears, he'll yell stuff for another 10s after (don't waste it before the boss actually comes :>)[/li]\r\n[li]keep FF and demo roar up at all times[/li]\r\n[li]keep lacerate up for more maul damage (you are specced for [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=51269][Rend and Tear][/url] right !)[/li]\r\n[li]berzerk in the start, get him down to 66%, shift out and heal up once he banishes[/li]\r\n[li]decurse yourself if needed, barkskin in caster form in case you are unlucky and get cought by screech when healing up[/li]\r\n[li]demo roar -> swipe+maul the small birds[/li]\r\n[li]repeat the same to 33% and then to 0%[/li]\r\n[li]If you are in trouble and on low hp (you may get unlucky and get caught by screech in caster form), use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=61336][Survival Instincts][/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=22842][Frenzied Regeneration][/url] together for better effect.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\nDone this several times in past weeks, whole run takes roughly 20 minutes this way.\r\nI'm using tanking spec and tanking gear with one on-use ap trinket. [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=40897][Glyph of Maul][/url] makes the trash clear much faster and safer.", "date": "2008-12-17T21:33:05-06:00", "rating": 30, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Why are you killing any trash outside of Anzu's room? It can all be easily stealthed past at 80.  Some good tips, but if you do not want to lose your mind kill the first boss.(Super easy) It sucks wiping on Anzu and having to clear the room trash again.", "creationdate": "2008-12-17T23:14:59-06:00", "id": 65697, "rating": 8, "commentid": 516780, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "22323", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed doable solo as a feral druid. Also, it is totally doable in quest and crafted blues / epics. Just be sure to heal whenever he self-banishes and you should be fine.", "creationdate": "2009-05-04T10:03:32-05:00", "id": 403955, "rating": 1, "commentid": 516780, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Arador", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "\"# Pull first two birds packs, wait for the serpent patrol and kill it. # Kill the last pack in front of two ravenguards. # Kill the ravenguard duo (these mobs are really nasty, make sure you root one before pull, and stun when they enrage).\"  Just want to add that those packs don't need to be killed, i usually skip them. And after 3.1 I'm doing it in my dps gear, full run takes no more than 12 minutes.", "creationdate": "2009-05-25T03:48:14-05:00", "id": 407655, "rating": 1, "commentid": 516780, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "pltr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 516929, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "zadiel", "body": "Yes, I'm sure it's possible. While it is easier in level 80 epics, the first time I did it I was still wearing mostly level 70 epics, so you should be fine even in level 80 blues.\r\n\r\nAs far as strategy, there's not much to it but I'll offer some insights:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Kill one of the other bosses to save yourself to the instance (in case you die, so the trash won't reset). I usually killed the first boss because he was on the way, but the last boss probably makes more sense to kill since he will open up the door from the beginning of the instance to the end. I only died a couple times while farming this, when I got feared into another group while clearing trash and my shadowmeld didn't work to drop combat.[/li]\r\n[li]I always cleared the room before summoning. It gives you a lot of room to run around during the fight.[/li]\r\n[li]On trash, you can outrange the fear from the prophets, and you can pop berserk to break the fear if you mess up. Everything else is pretty easy. I usually pulled with hibernate on a bird (if there was one) and entangling roots on any of the mobs besides the prophets, which I killed first. You don't need to CC, but it makes clearing the trash easier. Use barkskin on each trash pack; it should be up every time. If you need to pop cooldowns to survive, don't hesitate to; you can always wait a few minutes for them to come up.[/li]\r\n[li]Once you summon Anzu, he doesn't aggro immediately. I took this to my advantage and cast regrowth on the eagle (haste) and falcon (fire dmg) statues before the fight started.[/li]\r\n[li]Once you engage, keep up a 5-stack of lacerate, FF, and demoralizing roar. Mangle whenever it isn't on cooldown and spam swipe when mangle is on cooldown (but make sure to keep lacerate up). Save your barkskin for when he stuns you, and pop berserk after the first stun wears off (or before the first stun if your rage shoots up fast). Also, make sure you refresh your lacerate stack before he stuns you; the stun has a cast time. If you refresh lacerate before and after the stun, you won't lose the stack.[/li]\r\n[li]As soon as he banishes, cast regrowth on yourself (and more HoTs if necessary). Watch out for his curse; try to interrupt your spell and decurse yourself if possible. After casting regrowth on yourself, run away from him and put a HoT on the falcon statue (it does aoe dmg). Make sure you have time to switch to bear before he stuns you again (if this means you can't put a HoT on the statue, so be it). You can set your focus to him to make the stun cast more obvious. Use demoralizing roar on the adds and spam swipe/maul until they're dead. If something goes wrong during this part (i.e., you mess up), the distance you put between yourself and him will let you heal once or twice more.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nThat's basically it. Keep up your debuffs and rinse and repeat. If the #$%^ hits the fan, pop survival instincts and frenzied regeneration. The first few times I did this, I had a healthstone with me; it doesn't hurt.", "date": "2008-12-17T23:50:12-06:00", "rating": 36, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-28T23:32:44-05:00", 1, "zadiel"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 544091, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lighter", "body": "A good summary, I also found the following usefull.\r\n\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]After pulling, i would take the boss to the South West corner of the room, behind the stone box.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n[b][i]I found that he enters the first banishing phase on 75% Health, not 66%. I am unsure why that is.[/i][/b]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]When he banished, i would go to the opposite side of the box, out of Anzu's LoS. Here i can heal without getting the Spell Bomb Curse.[/li]\r\n[li]I cast Rejuvenation on the Eagle and entered bear form for the AoE phase. I then moved the mobs to the North West side of the room, behind another stone box. I used this macro to get them down fast. (I had the Maul glyph)[/li]\r\n[li][/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n[code]#showtooltp\r\n/cast maul\r\n/cast swipe[/code]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Once down, I could cast a few HoTs on myself before Anzu reached me. As i was out of LoS, Spell  Bomb didnt affect me.[/li]\r\n[li]I then took Anzu back to the South West Corner and repeated again at 33%.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nI got the Mount on my 5th attempt, don't give up!", "date": "2009-01-03T04:52:13-06:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
