{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 635763, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "111007", "body": "[u]How to solo as resto[/u]\r\n\r\nI've done this the past few days as resto, mostly out of boredom.  I strongly urge you to pay the 100g to respec feral and do a few dailies after to make up the difference in both time and money.  However, if you're stubborn like me, here's how I do it:\r\n\r\nALWAYS kill the first boss, you will probably wipe somewhere on the trash or the boss and it will all reset otherwise.  He's easy, just nuke, heal and barkskin+hurricane.\r\n\r\nThe trash in Anzu's room can be a real pain.  I wear the pvp trinket to remove fear.  Root the talon lords, sleep the birds, and cyclone the 2nd prophet if there is one.  Nuke the prophets first to avoid the fears.  You can use the coffin in the corner to kite.  They don't have much health but they do a good bit of damage if you don't CC them.  I recommend killing all 5 packs + serpent in the middle.  The 2 bird packs Anzu summons will social aggro them otherwise.\r\n\r\nWhen you summon Anzu, move to the wall, he won't attack you right away.  Now HOT up yourself and the eagle, and engage the boss.  You can keep the eagle hotted the whole fight to deal 300 DPS, I use rejuv.  Just make sure you do >50% of the damage to him (~125k).  alternate between bear and tree, and the goal here is to keep demo roar, lacerate, regrowth/rejuv on self, and rejuv on the eagle up at all times.  When you shift to bear stack a couple lifeblooms.  You can use frenzied rejuv about every phase.  Don't ever let your bear health drop below 60% unless your NS is up. The reason for this is that when you shift back to tree he will almost ALWAYS spell bomb you, which needs to be decursed before you cast a hot.  Rehot yourself, you'll probably use innervate around 80% and again at 20%, the mana issue isn't too bad if you're sitting in bear form enough of the fight.  Save barkskin for when you're stunned in tree, otherwise try to shift to bear before the screech finishes casting.  My damage breakdown usually looks like:\r\n\r\n30% hurricane (adds)\r\n23% lacerate\r\n20% thorns\r\n\r\nIf you can keep lacerate up, you don't have to worry about the eagle outdps'ing you.  Take your time and be sure to stay above 60% when you shift back to heal.  He'll crit you for 6-7k.\r\n\r\nTake your time", "date": "2009-03-08T14:52:04-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 646505, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Biggrim", "body": "Solo'ing Anzu as feral dps spec:\r\n\r\nIt IS possible, but much more difficult, to solo Anzu as a feral dps spec'd druid.  Here's how I do it.\r\n\r\n1)  Bring your tanking gear, and your frost resist gear\r\n\r\n2)  Stam stack!  I'm a pretty well-geared druid, I'm just over 40k hp self-buffed in bear form in my tanking gear + frost resist gear (which has only +24 stam gems)\r\n\r\n3)  Potions, scrolls, and healthstones help, if you have them!\r\n\r\n4)  Demoralizing roar is your friend!\r\n\r\nI always clear all the trash in Anzu's room, and the first and last bosses of the instance, before attempting the Raven God.  It just makes running back that much faster, and they're downright easy.  Upon summoning the boss, hang back.  He doesn't aggro right away, so put a regrowth on the eagle statue and the falcon statue.  Then charge in, mangle/maul/lacerate to get him to 75%, when he first disappears, and don't forget to keep demoralizing roar up.  Use your barkskin as soon as he first stuns you, and then every time thereafter that he stuns you and it's not on CD.\r\n\r\nPray you resist the curse.  If you don't it gets much harder, as you don't get to heal as much because you waste 2 gcd's decursing (the first being from the heal you stop because you got cursed in the middle of it!)   Still doable, however.  Throw a rejuvenate on the eagle statue, it speeds up downing the birds tremendously.  Then heal yourself.  You don't have to get yourself up to 100%, as you should be able to regain a few % from the birds.  Kite the birds as far away from the boss as you can and swipe-spam them down.  When Anzu comes out of his banished state, he will run around and kill whatever critters are in his aggro range before he comes to you, so you might be able to get off a lifebloom or rejuvenation or something quick.\r\n\r\nProceed to dps the boss down to 33%, when he will banish again.  You'll probably be pretty low on hp at that point, I'm usually around 30%.  Again, pray you resist the curse.  Heal like mad, rejuvenate the eagle, and berserk.  Get the birds down fast!  Heal up as much as you can once they're down, and prepare for the end.  Get the boss down as fast as you can, and pray you hit harder than he does.  Good luck!\r\n\r\nSome points to consider:  The fight takes me about 4 - 4 1/2 minutes.  So either I can burn an early frenzied regeneration, and use it again during the 3rd boss phase, or I can use it during the 2nd boss phase.  Demoralizing roar helps quite a bit, so use it!  I don't always get him on the first try, so be patient with it, and you will succeed!", "date": "2009-03-18T05:21:49-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
