{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 708059, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zorrah", "body": "He's only available on Heroic.\r\n\r\nI've been farming him solo for the last 2 weeks...every day.\r\n\r\nI'm feral tank specc'ed with full tier 7.5.  I run with just my buffs...about 36,500 health, 40% dodge and 28K armor or so.\r\n\r\nI don't have any real issues.  I've never had to heal myself by popping out of form.  I have used frenzied regeneration a few times....but ironically the groups are tougher than the boss. By the time the first banish hits and the adds come I'm around 32K health.   Swiping the adds I usually end back up at full health when he comes out of being banished.\r\n\r\nI can usually get the run done in just over 20 minutes.   I kill all the adds in his room and the 2 standing at the door..and the 1 pack outside.   \r\n\r\nKeep beserk saved for fear (to break it) as people have said.  Barkskin alot and heal between pulls.\r\n\r\nIt'll drop..eventually :)", "date": "2009-05-06T23:29:11-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 724220, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "chonchu", "body": "This boss is easy to solo as feral so I'll share a trick to solo this as resto/boomkin.\r\n\r\nI'm sure Blizz will nerf this but still - maybe someone out there can grab the mount before they do.\r\n\r\n1- Stealth all the way into the boss. \r\n2- Use Soothe Animal on the flying mob around the orb. When it pats to the back of the orb, go there and summon the boss and then back up at max range again. (or just kill it if you want).\r\n3- All you gotta do now is trow HoTs on the Eagle Spirit (closest one to your right).\r\n\r\nThere are like 4 bugs here.\r\n[ol]\r\n[li]The stone is suposed to do 300 damage to all enemies in the room - but it actually does only to the boss if you don't have anything agrroed.[/li]\r\n[li]The damage on the boss do not put you or the boss on  combat.[/li]\r\n[li]Even out of combat the health/mana regen on the boss is really low - like 500 health every 30sec.[/li]\r\n[li]The boss is supossed to summon the adds at 75%, 50% and 25% but since it's not in combat - it doesn't. [b]However for this to work - you gotta 1 shot it at the end.[/b] If you don't one shot it - then he'll banish himself and summon the adds and agrro pretty much the whole room.[/li]\r\n[/ol]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSo all you gotta do is keep the Eagle Spirit damaging the boss. \r\n[u][b]IT WILL TAKE YOU 45 MINUTES TO KILL THE BOSS THIS WAY![/b][/u]\r\n(Just letting you know before you come back complaining it takes fu***** forever - so grab a book).\r\n\r\nOnce the boss is at like 2k health left - do a starfire + moonfire combo.\r\n[b]You need to perform this one shot at the end to tab the loot table. [/b]\r\nThe flying snake will agrro - shadowmelt - Smooth it again and loot.\r\n\r\nGood Luck =)", "date": "2009-05-22T11:01:29-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 729539, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Phinx", "body": "How to solo Anzu as a balance druid: \r\n(By a resto druid that has no clue about balance druids)\r\n\r\nI dont have any feral gear, and found that hotting the Eagle for 45 minutes was way too boring, so I decided to give it a shot as Moonkin anyway. I used my usual Boomkin PvP spec, so it wasnt optimal for the purpose.\r\n\r\nWhat I did however, was changing two of my major glyphs to Lifebloom and Rejuvnation for some extra healing.\r\n\r\nA checklist of what you'll need before you head into Sethekk as Moonkin:\r\n\r\n - [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=46376]Flask of the Frost Wyrm[/url] (Extra healing and damage, and its not so pricey now that its only 1 hr)\r\n - A few stacks of [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=40093]Indestructible Potions[/url] 3500 extra armor is a ton of mitigation, especially when in caster form\r\n\r\nI dont have Moonkin gear either. So I used the only gear I have, resto PvP gear.\r\nMy stats buffed with flask,indestructible pot and MotW in Moonkin form:\r\n\r\n2682 SP\r\n25 haste rating\r\n12,40% crit\r\n21158 armor \r\n21900 HP\r\n14800 Mana\r\n236 MP5 while casting\r\n\r\nSo, now to the actual fight. Start off with stealthing to Ikiss, and kill him before you kill anything else. Killing him will open the shortcut to his room in case you should die, saving you a lot of time. It also gives you space to kite.\r\n\r\nStart killing off the packs one by one from his room. If there are birds in the pack, hibernate them. Root another moob and kill the rest.  Prophets should be your #1 kill priority, as they fear, but keep in mind that you can outrange their fear. Its has a very short range, if you keep moving you should never be feared.  Dotting and running works great, in the empty room of Ikiss you can also use Starfall without any troubles, and a fear wont kill you. Typhoon is great here.\r\n\r\nThe only hard trash is the Ravenguards by the entrance to Anzu's room. They hit like a truck, you simply cannot tank them. Start off by pulling one with Starfire and root the other.  Use your Treants on the Ravenguard that isnt rooted, and move backwards while your treants nuke the Ravenguard, dot him up. Go catform and dash away, or use Nature's Grasp to gain some distance while you finish him off. Just remember to root the second Ravenguard that will come for you, they burst pretty hard and Barkskin wont save you. Typhoon works on them, which can be a lifesaver.\r\n\r\n\r\nSo now you've cleared all the trash and Ikiss, when you know the packs it will take 15 minutes tops.\r\n\r\n\r\nP1: (100-66%)\r\nBefore you get in combat use a Indestructible Potion, so you can use a second when the 2 minutes are up. I usually start off with a regrowth on all the bird statues, drinking to full (takes 3 secs), then regrowthing and rejuvnating myself, go Moonkin, pull and pop Treants right off the bat. The reason I do this is so they get off CD to the last 33%, when you really need em.\r\nAnzu should drop to 66% really fast, you shouldnt go out of Moonkin form this first phase, as you wont have lost more than 6-7k HP with prehots at most.\r\n\r\nNote that you cannot kite Anzu. He will just reset if you pull him too far from his spawn.\r\n\r\n\r\nP2: (First wave of birds)\r\nIt will take a few seconds before the birds attack you. Use this time to throw up a few hots. Regrowth and Rejuvnation is great here, long hots that will last thru this phase. Be aware that Anzu can still stun you.\r\n\r\nWatch out for [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=40303]Spell Bomb[/url]. For me, Anzu usually uses it the first time when P2 starts. Instantly cancel your cast and decurse. The birds arent a big threat really. They hit for 200ish in Moonkin, and are easily AoEed down with Starfall and Hurricane, just wait till you have the Owlkin Frenzy proc so you dont waste half your hurricane.  \r\n\r\nP3: (66-33%)\r\nAnzu will rush you once all birds are down.  At this point I pop Barkskin, and start hotting up. I usually go Lifebloom - > Regrowth - > Lifebloom - > Rejuvnation - > Lifebloom - > Moonkin. \r\n\r\nAt this point you are probably OOM, if not earlier. Use Innervate, and you might need to refresh your Indestructible Potion. Getting hit in caster form without it means 4-5k hits, which translates into a quick death. In this phase you have no offensive cooldowns to use.Only your normal damage spells. You might need to heal twice or more, get as many hots as possible on before you go back to Moonkin, you dont want to waste mana, you really need to catch up when your HP is low. I wouldnt fall below 10-12k health before healing, then it starts to get really dangerous if you get unlucky with stuns and Spell Bombs when you pop out to heal.\r\n\r\nWhen you see him casting Paralyzing Screech (5 second cast time), 6 second AoE stun, throw a few hots on, and go back to Moonkin before its finished. If you use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=46081]Titan-forged Rune of Audacity[/url] (I did), you can trinket one stun.\r\n\r\nP4: (Second wave of birds)\r\nObviously same as first, but you need to keep enough mana to finish the last 33%. You wont have Starfall here, so wait for Owlkin Frenzy and Hurricane them down. You'll want to keep yourself at near full HP before the birds are dead and Anzu resumes his attacks, so hot yourself [i]before[/i] the birds attack you. If you go caster form to heal while you have the birds on you the damage might become a problem, especially if Anzu decides to stun you, and you also risk not getting the birds down before Anzu releases, which means you die.\r\n\r\nP5: (33-0%)\r\nWhen Barkskin is up, use it. When Treants are back up, use them. Starfall, use it. Just remember to keep yourself up, and you'll down him. When the Treants are back up he goes down like a rock, just be sure to keep your health pool up. When you pop out to heal, throw up Regrowth, Rejuvnation and 3x Lifebloom. I went OOM here, and had to wait for mana regen to pop my Treants. Luckily I had full hots on me at this time, so he went down with me at around 7k health and 1000 mana left.\r\n\r\n\r\nIt was my first kill so the strat isnt perfect for sure. I had around 11-12 tries before getting him down, but I think the next time it should take 1-3 tries tops, as it doesnt feel very random. Scrolls of Intellect / Spirit / Stamina would also be very helpful, but there wasnt any at a reasonable price available at the AH. Some PvE gear for mana regen would be nice too, but I wouldnt drop below 20k health.\r\n\r\n[url=http://eu.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Ravencrest&n=Phinx]Here[/url] is my armory profile, should show me in the gear that I used as I dont really have much else. My Moonkin spec might be slightly stupid, but I dont have a clue about Moonkins and only use it for fun in BGs / Duels and the odd heroic.\r\n\r\nGonna fraps it also, dont know how interesting it is but it should make the strat more clear than this mess.\r\n\r\nHappy farming = )\r\n\r\n[i]In before TL;DR, wall of text etc.[/i]", "date": "2009-05-27T19:09:26-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 737845, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "LockeColeMA", "body": "Nothing much to add to this... I've soloed this guy around 25 times and still no luck. As a feral druid it is simple. Tank spec gives you Improved LotP, and I enchanted my weapon with Lifeward. As stated, the groups in the room are tougher than Anzu himself. I really hate the packs with two Prophets; if you don't down them quick enough or get lucky and resist their fears, they will gladly chain fear you into other groups, leading quickly to death (or Shadowmeld). \r\n\r\nAnyway, a run in and out (killing all bosses because vendoring the items gets you a bit of gold) takes around 20 minutes total. Wish me luck on getting the mount; I saw it TWICE yesterday in Dalaran!", "date": "2009-06-05T08:55:50-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
