{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 748980, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Allilarsen", "body": "This can be semi-solo'd by an enhancement shaman.\r\n\r\nWhat you do is:\r\n\r\n1. Get a 2nd account and level a druid to 70 (using the RAF buff helps a lot)\r\n2. Make sure your shaman is good geared, Naxx 25 / Ulduar 10-25\r\n3. Enter Sethekk Halls and start to clear a way to Anzu. (Waiting for Spirit Wolfs to be ready for each group is a good idea.)\r\n4. When you get to Anzu's room, clear everything.\r\n5. (Optional) Kill the last boss so you have a short run if you wipe and if you take a break, the trash won't respawn.\r\n\r\nNow for the boss itself:\r\n\r\n1. When you summon / engage him, have your Spirit Wolfs ready.\r\n2. When the boss is engaged and the Spirit Wolfs are healing you for a good amount of health, swich over to your druid and use the macros posted above to hot the spirit birds.\r\n3. In p2, use Magma Totem and don't kill the last bird before you got enaugh health back.\r\n4. When you re-engage the boss, use Earth Elemental, swich over to your druid and hot up the birds before you go back to the shaman and start nuking.\r\n5. Aoe the birds again with Magma Totem, same as before.\r\n6. Now I use heroism and just nuke the boss for the last 30%.\r\n\r\n\r\nIt's not hard at all, atleast not the boss. The trash can be a pain but it's still doable.\r\n\r\n- Good luck!", "date": "2009-06-17T06:56:47-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I got this mount after +/- 40 runs.  When clearing Anzu's room its always a  good idea to zerg down the Prophets first, they present the most danger, getting feared into another pack is very hard to recover from.  Keep beserk handy for when you do get feared into an unluck position and break it before you get into trouble.   The boss itsself isnt all to hard in feral spec assuming your fairly geared.  Having done 196 runs for the baron mount the 40 runs i did for this pro druid mount where well worth it... gl on your hunt", "creationdate": "2009-06-27T02:43:58-05:00", "id": 106227, "rating": 1, "commentid": 748980, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "370352", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 42, "id": 769848, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "200692", "body": "Farming the mount now for a little over 2 weeks straight. Everyday the same thing: Prowl to boss room, clear trash, summon boss, kill boss, cross fingers, QQ in Gchat while I hearth and log on an alt.\n\nI'm beginning to lose hope. I'm seeing the mount more and more and I'm starting to wonder if this boss just hates me. To top it off, its every class EXCEPT druids who have the damn mount. You'd think that if you pulled your guildies into a run with you they would at least give you dibs on the mount since YOU have to summon it -.-\n\nWell it's a \"druid\" mount no doubt and anyone who \"isn't\" a druid can go fly a dragon kite if they were lucky enough to get it >.<\n\n[EDIT]\nFinally got it after 64 solo runs (not including the 30 or so I did before I started soloing it). HANG IN THERE!", "date": "2009-07-06T16:51:14-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "3rd month of farming every day here. Don't lose hope just yet. ;)   Also, not sure if it has been mentioned here or not: you don't have to kill the mobs in the upper left corner of Anzu's room. They won't aggro and it saves a little bit of time.", "creationdate": "2009-07-26T05:36:02-05:00", "id": 111863, "rating": 3, "commentid": 769848, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "336105", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-07-28T22:08:39-05:00", 1, "200692"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 772186, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "mouseno4", "body": "Ive been farming this boss, almost butt naked. Im wearing [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=21157]Festive Green Dress[/url]. I recently reset my talents for a bit of fun in another instance. They have yet to be set.\n\n[ul]\n[li]Prowl to Darkweave Syth's room. Dont kill anything. Once past the doorway, remove prowl and run around the edges of the room. Enter prowl again at the other doorway.[/li]\n[li]Prowl the entire way to Anzu's room. Dont kill anything. [/li]\n[li]Cast soothe animal on Cobalt Serpent. Walk up to Anzu's summoning stone. Summon Anzu. Back away almost to the previous doorwar.[/li]\n[li]Cast rejuvenation on Eagle Spirit for 40 mins.[/li]\n[li]When Anzu's health reaches ~1000-2000 health, 1 shot him with starfire or moonfire.[/li]\n[li]Recast soothe animal on Cobalt Serpent. Loot Anzu and possibly the mount.[/li]\n[li]Run out of heroic sethekk halls, and logout at entrance and play an alt. Or hearth out and do whatever you want.[/li]\n[/ul]\n\nIf the mount drops, grats! If not, come back tomorrow and repeat.", "date": "2009-07-08T21:03:09-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-07-08T21:14:43-05:00", 3, "mouseno4"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 44, "id": 772946, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "1wingedangel", "body": "is he still a druid required summon?", "date": "2009-07-09T15:29:08-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, I don't think he will EVER be summonable by other classes as he is the exclusive boss from the Druids' Swift Flight Form Quest Chain.", "creationdate": "2009-07-12T10:57:29-05:00", "id": 109254, "rating": 5, "commentid": 772946, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zalafina", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 45, "id": 784807, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "zanetheinsane", "body": "Even if you are a very poorly geared feral tank Anzu should be a freebie. With a little Naxx-10 gear, some heroism-badge gear, and a couple valor-badge pieces (the cloak and ring), and even some heroic dungeon gear still, the fight should require very little strategy.\r\n\r\nAs long as you have Improved Leader of the Pack you'll most likely end the fight at full life or close to it. Activate barkskin during the 5 second stun, keep demoralizing roar up, and just mash on buttons (mangle, lacerate, swipe, FFF).\r\n\r\nWhen the adds spawned I just swipe-spammed and didn't bother with maul so that I could build up 100 rage to dump some more damage on Anzu. When Anzu came out of immunity, even if I had adds up I just went back to swiping him. The adds do so little damage they'll likely kill themselves on thorns eventually. They hit for around 100ish and aren't much of a threat even with a few of them. If anything they were giving me more rage to dump on Anzu.\r\n\r\nFor comparison, I've got 35k HP, 27k Armor, 34% Dodge in Bear Form. If you are around these stats or even slightly below you shouldn't have to worry about strategy or planning or placement. Don't worry about dragging the adds behind a box or what skills the boss has or keeping friendly adds alive. Just go in their and faceroll him, pretty much.", "date": "2009-07-21T19:45:01-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 46, "id": 795992, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vtai", "body": "Finally got Anzu on my third run. Yes 3rd run, I consider myself real lucky. It was very easy for me since Im a feral Druid in Naxx gear. The hardest part was clearing his room. When there was a pack of 2 prophets I would just root one and kill the other one real fast. Feral charge plus bash would keep them stunned long enough so they can't fear. Anzu was an easy kill. Just made sure I healed myself when i had to during this banish stage. Now time to farm ZG for the tiger mount.", "date": "2009-08-02T14:43:53-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 47, "id": 802853, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "413018", "body": "could a lv 70-75 druid solo him? you could stealth there in cat form", "date": "2009-08-07T18:09:16-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Very possible. Right now as an ulduar geared moonkin, it -seems- impossible to solo him one on one, firstly, the trash hits hard...it isn't worth clearing the whole room.  Second, I get destroyed on add phase.  But- it is possible to 'cheat' on the solo.  Just keep hots on the eagle while watching a movie, then when he has 2-3k left starfire him and loot.   The person below me is only half wrong, he shouldn't really have gotten downranked. The trash is a HUGE pain to clear, and you'll probably die at least once if you don't wait for cooldowns, at least as a moonkin.", "creationdate": "2009-09-11T04:27:15-05:00", "id": 121427, "rating": 3, "commentid": 802853, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "281730", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 48, "id": 803375, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "kabookiejoe", "body": "no if ur lvl 75 ur gonna get destoryed.  not to mention that room is a real pain to clear.\n\n\nbut if you're gonna try and clear it at 80, prophets in his room should die first, that fear is the end of me most times\n\n\n\nlol, downranked by morons who never been there, they should remove this + minus crap from the site.", "date": "2009-08-08T04:56:34-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "kabookiejoe is completely right.  The comments in here stating that Anzu and trash is a breeze in a few heroics and/or naxx feral gear is a stretch.  70-75s would not do so well there alone.", "creationdate": "2009-08-17T12:43:47-05:00", "id": 116750, "rating": 3, "commentid": 803375, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kururin55", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-08-17T07:52:00-05:00", 1, "kabookiejoe"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 49, "id": 816983, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "431169", "body": "Sorry for asking stupid question, but i need to be surely clear. Can i obtain Raven Lord, when i am not Druid? Also please don'T downrate, i need to know it, thanks for response.", "date": "2009-08-19T16:55:39-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, you can, as long as you have a Druid summon Anzu for you. He can ONLY be summoned by Druids on the last step of their Swift Flght Form quest using the Essence-Infused Moonstone, or by those who have already completed the entire questline and talked to the NPC to get another Essence-Infused Moonstone.", "creationdate": "2009-08-20T04:47:34-05:00", "id": 117335, "rating": 5, "commentid": 816983, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zalafina", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 50, "id": 825264, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "246372", "body": "When you solo him, make sure to kill all adds in the room first. Otherwise they will aggro in the first Banish phase, when all the raven adds spawn.\r\n\r\nEven with two healing trinket ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=27921]Mark of Conquest[/url] + [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=19287]Darkmoon Card: Heroism[/url]) + Ulduar Tank Gear I didnt have a change against the whole room + Anzu + raven adds", "date": "2009-08-28T10:24:03-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 51, "id": 857275, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "48858", "body": "I comfirm Resto Druid Spec PVP can easy Clear all Room in 30 Min Trash and 8 more Anzu the Raven God .\r\n\r\nIf its drop 100 % ur but take mutch more Time .\r\n\r\nI used Glyph of Barkskin + 2 points on Improved Barkskin and points on Insect Sawrm\r\n\r\n2200 SP i solo him\r\n\r\nKill Time-Lost Controller as Priority \r\nAnd Kite Each Group Around Chest whit all DOTS its take Few minutes each Group\r\n\r\nUR NOOB AND CANT SOLO AGAIN AND AGAIN \r\n\r\nHeal this Birst they will HELP u alote to kill him\r\n\r\nBird Statues\r\nWhen Anzu is summoned, three friendly NPC bird statues appear as well. Casting a druid HoT on the birds will awaken them for the HoT's duration, and will provide the following effects to the group:\r\n\u25a0Hawk Spirit (left): Grants Protection of the Hawk. All players receive 500 less damage from every attack. Applied before armor.\r\n\u25a0Eagle Spirit (right): Grants Spite of the Eagle. Deals 300 damage every second to all enemies in the room.\r\n\u25a0Falcon Spirit (back): Grants Speed of the Falcon. Gives 25% movement speed increase, 25% ranged haste and 25% spell casting haste.\r\n \r\nHope This Comment will Help Druid Resto SPec Only", "date": "2009-10-01T23:41:14-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
