{"commentv2": 1, "number": 70, "id": 1053134, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "executable", "body": "I have a druid character and a warrior character , and i want the mount on my warrior , can i summon this NPC on my druid , re-log on my warrior *assuming they are in the same party* and it will be there or does it despawn ? thanks.", "date": "2010-06-06T04:39:36-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "How will get them in the same party? Both characters need to be online to make a party invite and you can't log in with different characters on the same account. Only way would be for the characters to be on different accounts, and then there would be no problem having both online at the same time in the instance.", "creationdate": "2010-08-08T18:18:52-05:00", "id": 176830, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1053134, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Endev", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
