{"commentv2": 1, "number": 73, "id": 1077422, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Raziya", "body": "I just soloed this...as a shadow priest. Yes, it was very hard. I died probably 10 times before I finally got him, but it was worth it. I used my druid alt to summon him, and was able to bring my priest in there to kill Anzu by having a guild mate in the group with my druid while I cleared all the trash and summoned Anzu on her. Once I had summoned Anzu on my druid, I alt+f4 and then had my guild mate invite my priest to the group, which allowed me to have Anzu up in her instance.\n\nI didn't use any potions/flasks, but they might have made things a little bit easier. I am in partial ICC25/10 gear, with a GS of about 5800. I relied a lot on vampric embrace for healing, with clever uses of dispersion when he would stun me with the bird adds all over my face.\n\nI had to time my heals and use PoM/renew/shield to stay alive when he spellbombed me, as I am a priest and cannot dispel curses.\n\nSo fear not, squishies! It can be done...I love this mount and determined to get it, and now that I know I can solo it on my priest I am looking forward to getting to do it every day =)\n\nEdit: I finally got Anzu to drop his mount last night! =) I am so psyched!", "date": "2010-07-10T12:11:17-05:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-07-22T18:26:09-05:00", 1, "Raziya"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 74, "id": 1086240, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "548924", "body": "Soloed in cat spec & gear (GS 4625) / bear form (about 26k health). Died the first time because I'm a newb and panicked during the banish/birds. Second time it was quite simple. My health didn't drop below 2/3 until after the second banish, and I still had my cooldowns.\n\nClearing the room was harder than the boss I'd agree.\n\nNo mount yet, but I'm going back tomorrow night. He's too cool to pass up.", "date": "2010-07-22T00:01:32-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-07-22T00:02:34-05:00", 1, "548924"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 75, "id": 1087133, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "236141", "body": "Went in last night to give this a go and didn't find it as easy as some people make it out to be. The trash took a little bit of time, but proper CC'in makes it fairly easy.\r\n\r\nI am currently Balance and just sat back and HoT'd up the Eagle for a while, got impatient and went to engage. Did this for a few tries before I decided to call it quits. I would think it is possible to just sit back and HoT the Eagle and just let that tick away, but that would be like a 20min wait before engaging to finish him off. Might look into grabbing some Feral gear before I work it again.\r\n\r\nIf anyone has any better ideas, I am all for it.", "date": "2010-07-23T08:06:11-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "What is your gear like? I definitely understand how hard it can be to solo, as a clothie who has soloed Anzu (it's hard!) Are you an engineer? I would have to use rocket boots if he spell bombed me at a bad time since I can't dispel curses like you can as a druid (I am a priest!). I would make sure you are dispelling the spell bomb since that is gonna be your #1 issue, and keep yourself hotted up. Barkskin through paralyzing screech if it hits you at a bad time - hurricane the birds when they spawn. Keep a health pot for emergencies - I did end up having to pot on a few of my runs. As a caster", "creationdate": "2010-07-23T08:06:12-05:00", "id": 455389, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1087133, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Raziya", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 76, "id": 1089420, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "354046", "body": "Just soloed him as a balance druid. The important thing is dispelling the Spell Bomb curse. The curse does not end when it deals its damage, it just keeps hitting you every time you cast a spell over its duration, so that [i]has[/i] to go before you finish casting your current spell or refreshing your HoTs; it's like standing in the fire.\r\n\r\nI'd recommend keeping the Hawk and Falcon spirits up and not wasting a cooldowns on the Eagle. It took me three or four tries to work out the details, but now that I've got it figured out I'm pretty sure I'll be able to get it in one try most of the time from now on. HoT yourself and the spirits up and nuke him down through the first phase, then HoT again and take care of the adds. If you get stunned while in caster form you could be in trouble. The main thing, though, is Spell Bomb and dispelling it.", "date": "2010-07-26T08:02:28-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 77, "id": 1096322, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Holyheadshot", "body": "This just dropped for me, and yes, it was my first kill o.O. Didn't really believe my eyes but it was there for sure :D. Another amazing thing was that right before I went Sethekk Halls I had been in Zul Gurub and won the tiger :D Kinda lucky day really ^^", "date": "2010-08-05T18:08:54-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "No offense but... how is this comment helpful to anyone?", "creationdate": "2014-04-10T03:09:46-05:00", "id": 739684, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1096322, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Eido", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-08-05T18:11:39-05:00", 1, "Holyheadshot"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 78, "id": 1097377, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "638939", "body": "After quite a few attempts I figured out how to solo Anzu as Boomkin spec, it seems a bit harder than Feral but it works. I was in icc10/25 gear.\r\n\r\nHave a pvp trinket equipped.\r\n\r\nStart the fight with Treants and an Insect Swarm, while the Treants are tanking Anzu, throw a Regrowth on the Falcon Spirit and a rejeuv on yourself. Switch to nuking Anzu. With the haste buff from the Falcon, he should get down to the first immune phase before you take any major damage. When he immunes, put 3 lifeblooms, a rejeuv and regrowth on yourself and starfall/hurricane to clear all the birds. If Paralysing Screech happens, PvP trinket it. Make sure to dispel Spell Bomb because it hurts ><\r\n\r\nWhen it goes to Anzu again, you'll still have HoT's on you from the immune phase, so you shouldn't take too much damage. Remember to keep dispelling Spell Bomb. If Paralysing Screech happens this time, use Barkskin to tank the damage. When he immunes again, once again put hots on yourself before all the birds start attacking and hurricane them down (starfall won't be off cooldown by this point). Before the last bird dies try to refresh hots on yourself as you won't have anything to keep yourself alive during Paralysing Screech if he casts it again if you don't have hots rolling. \r\n\r\nIt took me a few attempts to get right but it works fine. Just hope it drops for me sometime now :D Good luck!", "date": "2010-08-08T16:51:33-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 79, "id": 1099630, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "631387", "body": "I see a lot of comments where people solo him as a feral druid, but I can say that this is [u][b]possible as a balance druid[/b][/u] as well.\r\n\r\nBefore you summon the boss Anzu:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][b]Clear trash[/b]: There are 4 packs of mobs + 1 Serpent + another pack in the next room where the final boss is. Cast [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=53308]Entangling Roots[/url] on the Talon Lord or on the Prophet if there isn't a Talon Lord in the pack. Cast [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=18658]Hibernate[/url] on the Hawks. Before every pull I cast Regrowth and Rejuvenation on myself, safety above all.[/li]\r\n[li][b]Kill [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=18473]Talon King Ikiss[/url][/b]: Why? Because it opens a gate that opens a shortcut to Anzu. Saves time. This boss is quite easy. Again, keep yourself up with Regrowth & Rejuv although, you won't be needing this as much though.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nSummoning and killing Anzu:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][b]Positioning[/b]: I'm standing in the north-western corner of the room ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/maps?data=3791:287413]click for a map[/url]). This makes it easy to cast Regrowth on the Bird Statues.[/li]\r\n[li][b]Start of the fight[/b]: Before you pull, cast Regrowth on the Hawk Spirit & Falcon Spirit. Then cast Regrowth and Rejuv on yourself. Quickly get in Moonkin Form and start spamming Wrath > Insect Swarm > Moonfire > Eclipse > Starfire on Anzu (or whatever your favorite rotation is). Don't waste your Starfall yet![/li]\r\n[li][b]66%, Anzu banishes[/b]: Immune to all attacks. You have quite some time here to heal yourself up and if you get the chance throw a Regrowth on the Falcon Spirit as well. But watch out for the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=40303]Spell Bomb[/url]! Dispel this before you cast anything else. Now when all birds are attacking you, pop Starfall. This kills them quickly, except if you're affected by [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=40184]Paralyzing Screech[/url]. If this happens and you already used Starfall then don't kill the birds with Hurricane, no, first renew both Regrowth and Rejuvenation and then finish the birds with Hurricane. At this time, Anzu will become attackable again.[/li]\r\n[li][b]33%, Anzu banishes[/b]: Same story as at 66%. Best time to cast Barkskin is between 66% and 33%. Because your heals might run out before you get Anzu to 33% and the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=40199]Flesh Rip[/url] + Paralyzing Screech + Anzu attacking you, might kill you.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\nKey mechanics to this fight:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][b]Decurse [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=40303]Spell Bomb[/url][/b]: Top priority.[/li]\r\n[li][b]Hots running when affected by [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=40184]Paralyzing Screech[/url][/b]: This spell is cast by Anzu and has a 5 second cast time. Plenty of time to get some heals on you.[/li]\r\n[li][b]Focus on Anzu[/b]: I never target anything else then Anzu during the fight. Use macro's (few posts above mine) for targeting the statues.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nAbout the banish phases: When you are attacking Anzu and he gets to a certain amount of health, he will stop attacking you and banish. But the time between those two is a second or two. If you're doing 6k dps here you will get him between 50 and 75%.\r\n\r\nI still don't have the mount. I'm trying this every day and every day I one-shot Anzu, but I still kill Talon King Ikiss for the shortcut.", "date": "2010-08-12T03:15:06-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 80, "id": 1114440, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "519868", "body": "Oh dear God, I was getting so enraged trying this as a boomkin. I couldn't even clear the trash in his room. Try not to tear your hair out attempting this. I imagine feral would make this smoother.", "date": "2010-09-06T01:33:46-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Well...you can always kill 1 group/minute with starfall :)", "creationdate": "2010-10-02T17:28:09-05:00", "id": 184772, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1114440, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mroz123", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 81, "id": 1116853, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "blackksabbath", "body": "For the record, this is soloable as boomkin. What I do is stealth to the last boss and kill him, then kill the group of mobs in his room, then pull each other pack in Anzu's room 1 by 1 being careful I don't pull the 2 guards.\r\n\r\nTo kill Anzu: \r\nStep 1: I start off with starfire, moonfire,  insect swarm, starfall and get him to about 35 - 55% (It can be easier if you regrowth the bird furthest from the last bosses room, it gives you haste). I then spam click my decursive after he goes immune, wait for the stun then AoE down the birds, making sure ive got a regrowth and rejuv, and even a few lifeblooms on me if im low HP.\r\n\r\nStep 2: I spam click my decursive again waiting for the curse, pop trees, moonfire, insect swarm, warth untill immune, then repeat step 1.\r\n\r\nOccasionally I make stupid mistakes and he kills me but its very possible. Word of advise, try not to tank him in Tauren form :)\r\n\r\nSonicbloom - Cho'Gall", "date": "2010-09-09T11:31:12-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 82, "id": 1124628, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "28618", "body": "In Sumerian myth, Anzu was a large bird (eagle or vulture) who lived in the realm of the gods. He was originally a benign creature, but sometime around 2000BC, stories formulated that he rebelled against the gods.\r\n\r\nThe god Enlil had a number of objects that he would bestow some of his power into and which would then become a source of power for the gods. In Enlil's case, one of his main sources of power was his insignia, which included a list of all the \"destinies\" he had decided his subjects would accomplish (called a Tablet of Destinies). One day while the god was bathing, he took off his insignia and the register of destinies and put it aside. Anzu, who happened to be Enlil's guard, watched the god with envy and decided to make his move.\r\n\r\n    \"[i]I shall take the gods\u00b4 Tablet of Destinies for myself,\r\n    And control the orders for all the gods,\r\n    And shall possess the throne and be master of the rites!\r\n    I shall direct every one of the Igigi![/i]\"\r\n    He plotted opposition in his heart\r\n    And at the chamber\u00b4s entrance from which he often gazed,\r\n    He waited for the start of the day.\r\n    While Enlil was bathing in the holy water,\r\n    Stripped and with his crown laid down on the throne,\r\n    He gained the Tablet of Destinies for himself,\r\n    Took away the Enlil-power. Rites were abandoned,\r\n    Anzu flew off and went into\r\n    Radiance faded, silence reigned\r\n\r\nEnlil was enraged by this action and called a meeting among all the gods to find a champion who would fight against Anzu, regain the Tablet of Destinies, and set the word right again. After a number of gods refused the task, believing it to be impossible, Ninurta agreed to the mission.\r\n\r\nSoon, a battle ensued between Ninurta and Anzu. Ninurta called upon 'the seven winds' and shot at him with arrows, but the great bird held the Tablet of Destinies, which deflected all attacks against him.\r\n\r\n    As Anzu shouted at it:\r\n    \"[i]You, shaft that came, return to your reed thicket!\r\n    Bow frame, back to your copse!\r\n    Bow string, back to the ram\u00b4s gut! Feathers, return to the birds![/i]\"\r\n    He was holding the gods\u00b4 Tablet of Destinies in his hand,\r\n    And they influenced the string of the bow, the arrows did not come near his body\r\n    Deadly silence came over the battle and conflict ceased.\r\n    Weapons stopped and did not capture Anzu amid the mountains.\r\n\r\nWhen that approach failed, Ninurta tried a different strategy designed to tire out the bird - he went after Anzu's feathers, cutting them, and then pierced him with arrows. When the bird fell, he cut his throat.\r\n\r\n    Anzu grew weary and in the clash of tempests shed his pinions.\r\n    He (Ninurta) took a throw-stick to follow his arrows,\r\n    And cut off his pinions, detached both right and left.\r\n    He (Anzu) saw his wings and emitted his utterance.\r\n    But as he shouted 'Wing to wing' a shaft came up at him\r\n    A dart passed through his very heart.\r\n    He (Ninurta) made an arrow pass through pinion and wing,\r\n    A dart passed through heart and lungs,\r\n    He slew the mountains, inundated their proud pastures,\r\n    Inundated the broad earth in his fury,\r\n    Inundated the midst of the mountains, slew wicked Anzu,\r\n    And warrior Ninurta regained the Tablets of Destinies for his own hand.\r\n\r\nSource: http://www.deliriumsrealm.com/delirium/articleview.asp?Post=95", "date": "2010-09-21T07:22:55-05:00", "rating": 64, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
