{"commentv2": 1, "number": 92, "id": 1143839, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "insane822", "body": "Anzu will now always be spawned, with trash removed. No druid needed :)\r\n\r\n\r\nBlue Confirmed:\r\nhttp://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.html?topicId=27291811693&pageNo=1&sid=1#4", "date": "2010-10-15T22:38:05-05:00", "rating": 21, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 93, "id": 1143899, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "wesleyshawn05", "body": "No longer need the druid as stated before.  He is easily soloable as a 80 hunter.  Took me a few tries until I figured out the trick.  The problem is the birds that he spawns.  When Anzu banishes himself at 66% and is preparing to sick the birds on you, just feign death.  The birds wont attack you and will focus on your pet.  I had a turtle tank for me, and he was fine taking the damage.  Once Anzu comes out of banishment you can proceed burning him down (check your pets health and heal if necessary).  He will banish again at 33%.  Rinse and repeat until dead.", "date": "2010-10-16T00:43:47-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 94, "id": 1143911, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "28341", "body": "Very easily solo'd as a 80 combat rogue in ICC 25 gear. Recuperate made the fight trivial.\r\n\r\nGood luck farming him :D", "date": "2010-10-16T01:18:04-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 95, "id": 1144051, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "N0bby", "body": "Since patch [b]4.0.1[/b] you [b]DO NOT NEED[/b] a druid to summon Anzu. Happy mount farming!", "date": "2010-10-16T05:56:25-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 96, "id": 1144108, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "351814", "body": "Ok, I killed him yesterday as a Shadow Priest, however, today he is not there? Is it a once a week thing, or maybe a seperate timer to the instance?", "date": "2010-10-16T07:16:36-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It's a one day lock he should be spawned in Heroic mode.", "creationdate": "2010-10-16T09:55:30-05:00", "id": 460579, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1144108, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Doomzzg", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "May I ask you or any other priest that managed to kill him what is the best tactic?  I've tried few times but I can only get him to 50% or so, after birds get spawned Im usually unable to kill them fast enough and I just can't catch up on dmg and healing after that. Also the \"no casting for 6sec\" debuff along with stuns are causing lots of problems considering mind sear needs to be channeled. Should I try to go disc/holy and holy nova spam? Or is there some other way?  Thanks in advance.", "creationdate": "2010-10-16T10:44:02-05:00", "id": 460583, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1144108, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "681253", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I have, disc priest with mostly t9 gear bought with badges. :) Just keep your shield up, kill the birds with Holy Nova and be aware when you have spellbomb. Also keep your dots on his as they don't count when you have spellbomb on. Just blow cd's if you get into trouble, PI when it's off cd. The fight took me about 5 minutes, but I was able to down him without going below 40% health.", "creationdate": "2010-10-16T12:08:18-05:00", "id": 460591, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1144108, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "meowsmix", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yeah, I figured disc is much more comfortable way to kill him than shadow. Thanks for tips, now I just need RNG gods to give me the mount :)", "creationdate": "2010-10-16T13:02:13-05:00", "id": 460595, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1144108, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "681253", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "And just to show you he does still drop the mount, here's the  [url=http://i245.photobucket.com/albums/gg61/royalberry-/WoWScrnShot_101610_132525.jpg]killshot[/url] from today about 20 minutes after I left you that comment!", "creationdate": "2010-10-16T16:42:50-05:00", "id": 460606, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1144108, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "meowsmix", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 97, "id": 1144241, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zeqp", "body": "As of 4.0.1 this no longer requires a druid to summon the boss. It now spawns randomly, you can tell if he spawns by looking for an emote in your chat log as you enter the instance.\r\n\r\nProof: http://i44.photobucket.com/albums/f26/nivekks/gm-1.png", "date": "2010-10-16T10:03:53-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 98, "id": 1144438, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "126061", "body": "1) he does indeed always spawn now, just soloed him on my DK.\n2) for DKs attempting to solo it, beware that nor anti-magic shell nor icebound fortitude protects you from the stun effect on paralyzing screech. I had no problems soloing him (didn't drop below 95%) but I have an average ilvl of 251 so... o_O\nIf you're in blues, lower lvl than 80 or attempting it as dps you might want to make sure your HP stays high enough to survive being stunned at all times\nedit: and this can probably counts for all classes so CloS and such won't protect you from it either, though DS and IB probably do.", "date": "2010-10-16T13:52:19-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-16T13:55:00-05:00", 1, "126061"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 99, "id": 1144731, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "664031", "body": "For priests, it's easier solo him as Discipline or Holy than shadow. Just focus on healing yourself (mainly with Renew, PoM and shielding), and DoT's will do the trick. I'm inclined to believe that the gear you'll need must be higher than an average plate wearer or pet owner, but still... it's better than depending on not-always-there-to-help-after-I-got-my-own-mount friends.", "date": "2010-10-16T20:31:06-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I disagree with this. It is possible to solo him in shadow.  I've done it successfully with no wipe two days in a row.   When spell bomb hits - don't cast anything. I would sometimes pop a renew or a flash heal if i was in dire need of hp, but for the most part his hits were tolerable - I also use glyph of inner fire to increase armor for this fight.  [b]When adds come out - instead of mind sear i used holy nova to keep myself healed and keep dmg on the adds. [/b]This helped alot for those times when spell bomb hit. Also - health pots are not spells, so keep one handy in case you need a desper", "creationdate": "2010-10-16T20:31:07-05:00", "id": 461140, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1144731, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "aggr1103", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 100, "id": 1144803, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "449056", "body": "Just solo'd as an Arcane mage as of patch 4.0.1 in average ilvl 264 gear.  Strategy is fairly simple.  I would put this fight on par with something like the Delrisssa encounter in Magister's Terrace as far as strategy and difficulty are concerned.  I blow arcane power at the start only.  I save Mirror Images and Iceblock (Paralyzing Screech) for after the 2nd wave of adds.  Glyph of Evocation is very helpful.  This seems to be a pretty flawless strategy if executed properly.  Enjoy.", "date": "2010-10-16T22:29:43-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-16T22:37:20-05:00", 1, "449056"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 101, "id": 1145039, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Jademalo", "body": "I was a bit apprehensive after reading he was already summoned, since the way me and my druid mate used to do it was hed stealth through, kill the last boss, id then run up through the exit ramp and help to clear the room.\r\n\r\nSo when i heard it was always there, I decided to start solo farming, since my druid mate moved server. We must have killed it about 130 times togeather.\r\n\r\nI was pleasantly suprised at how easy it was to get to anzu's room with rocket boots and feign. Must have only taken 6 minutes or so.\r\n\r\nGetting to his room, i was thrilled that the trash was gone! And it was easy from there.\r\n\r\nAs BM, rhino, in, MD always up with the glyph, keep pummeling him, feign when the birds come out, they go to the rhino, (due to lack of volley) and multi shot all of them dead. Rinse and repeat, didnt even need to use mend pet.\r\n\r\nVery easy boss for a hunter, and I imagine when people have camo, it will be stupidly easy to solo.\r\n\r\nGood luck!\r\n\r\n(132 and counting..)", "date": "2010-10-17T04:44:34-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I am also using same strat as you to get to him haha. Except ive got two pairs of rocket boots so the cd is shorter :)", "creationdate": "2010-10-21T07:36:34-05:00", "id": 461031, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1145039, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Raginbum1", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 102, "id": 1145106, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "48636", "body": "Easy as a protection paladin with an average item level of 204. \r\n\r\nFirst of all, you can run past most mobs in the instance and the first boss if you stick  to the wall in his room. You only have to fight those that stand in doorways.\r\n\r\nThe fight against Anzu is easy. Just use Avenging Wrath and Divine Protection when they are available and heal yourself with Holy Power/Word of Glory. Other than that its just tank and spank.\r\n\r\nI used Seal of Insight, Blessing of Kings and Devotion Aura.", "date": "2010-10-17T06:21:50-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 103, "id": 1145117, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lethorio", "body": "As of 4.0.1, you no longer need a Druid to summon Anzu, so anyone can go into the instance and kill him.", "date": "2010-10-17T06:31:33-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As a druid, I no longer feel special :<", "creationdate": "2010-10-17T17:34:58-05:00", "id": 187207, "rating": 17, "commentid": 1145117, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jaru", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 104, "id": 1146590, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "gnorkthedark", "body": "as of 4.0.1 this is easy soloable by a rogue, just keep reoccupation up and dps like normal, evasion when needed.", "date": "2010-10-18T14:38:57-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 105, "id": 1146731, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "error10", "body": "Frost mages (and anyone else) should remember that there are two add phases before deciding when to blow cooldowns. This was indeed not a trivial fight in ICC25 gear with a freshly built frost spec, and I only got it on the second attempt.\n\nHow I did it:\n\nPositioned water elemental behind Hawk Spirit, 90 degrees across the room to the left. I stayed in the doorway. Let pet pull and get a few shots in. Nuked Anzu for all I was worth from max range until adds spawned. Each phase without adds runs like this: Nuke Frostbolt, Frostfire Bolt when Brain Freeze procs, and Deep Freeze whenever it's off cooldown and Fingers of Frost procs. (This is the typical frost rotation.)\n\nAdd phases: First phase I popped Mirror Image (because I forgot there were two phases) and they kept the birds busy while I rained a couple of Blizzards on them. Second add phase I had to get a bit more creative. Hit Frost Nova to get some range and then Blizzard a couple of times. Cone of Cold for any that get back in range. Anzu stuns you shortly after these phases begin, so you have to be able to ride it out. Make sure Ice Barrier is always up, and don't waste your Deep Freeze cooldown on the adds.\n\nFinal phase: He Cycloned me at the start of this phase and went after my pet. After that ended I was taking damage so I hit Ice Block to let my pet gain some more aggro and let my Ice Barrier cooldown run down. (I was reserving Cold Snap in case something went really wrong, but I didn't need it.) Then Blink for range and nuke until dead.\n\nHad Evocation, Ice Barrier, Frostbolt and Deep Freeze (among others not relevant here) glyphed.\n\nThings that might have helped: Cold Snap (as mentioned before) and PvP trinket (not sure if this works though). I popped Lifeblood (herbalism ability) once. A healing pot might also have been useful. I didn't hit Evocation on my successful attempt; I tried it on my first attempt but it was a complete waste of time and resulted in the wipe.\n\nEDIT: Downrated? You people don't deserve any help.", "date": "2010-10-18T16:48:06-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-11-29T11:30:47-06:00", 1, "error10"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 106, "id": 1146964, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "683747", "body": "Hey !\nI just got my reputation to honored today and I did a first try on this boss, and I looted it the mount ! I was amazed lol.\nI can confirm that you don't need a druid anymore, as I'm a warlock and the boss was there !", "date": "2010-10-18T22:02:40-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-18T22:05:01-05:00", 1, "683747"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 107, "id": 1147707, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "banchee2003", "body": "Soloed as a level 80 Holy Paladin. Just keep constant Exorcism and Judgements up, Consecrate when there are adds, and make sure Retribution Aura is up. Long, but easy to do.", "date": "2010-10-19T15:40:20-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 108, "id": 1148320, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "AzureusPT", "body": "As patch 4.0.1 Anzu is just standing in the room, you don't need to bring a druid to summon it. Also all the room is cleared, so you don't have to clean the pulls first.\r\n\r\nAs Elemental/Restoration shaman is easily soloable. With Elemental you have to be a little careful with your HP/mana but the fight is pretty straight and kinda fast. With Restoration there's no problem with your HP or mana but the fight takes a little longer due to the lack of DPS.\r\n\r\nI'm sure many other classes can easily solo it for the mount. Just watch for the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=18322]Sethekk Ravenguard[/url], they hit for a lot when enraged and you can die if you don't watch your HP.\r\n\r\nHappy hunting!", "date": "2010-10-20T09:56:02-05:00", "rating": -4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 109, "id": 1148495, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "47405", "body": "Tried soloing Anzu at the start of WotLK as moonkin but with no success. Now after 4.0.1 hit and with the new abilities and spells I gave it another shot and it worked. By keeping the Hawk and Eagle spirits up, HoTing yourself, applying DoTs and just spam Moonfire (and casting starsurge when shooting stars proc) it wasn't that hard killing him so if you lack the feral gear but got balance  give it a try!\r\n\r\nHad mostly ilvl 264 gear with 8203 armor (35%) outside of moonkin form (+10k if in, ~54%) since you need to HoT yourself and Anzu was hitting for around 3-4k.", "date": "2010-10-20T13:11:49-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 110, "id": 1148577, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "356951", "body": "Been farming on my Druid for quite some time, still no drop? :( Anything special you have to do? \r\n\r\nAlso if it is farmable, thinking of taking my other alts to farm the mount, do you still need to be attuned for levle 70 heroics in order to enter the instances (Outland dungeons)?", "date": "2010-10-20T15:12:52-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 111, "id": 1148752, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "NeverFinal", "body": "Playing a shadow spec priest this fight is tough. I cant get around the bird adds. I get stunned every few seconds and cant kill them with Mind Sear. Raven Lord is one of my most favorite mounts in the game and I really wanna be able to solo this. Any suggestions? Ive never played Holy or Disc but Im willing to try if it means I can do this fight easier. The damn curse is hurting the most.\n\nUpdate. Finally did it. When the adds come up i spam tab each one and put pain on all of them. Then simply stand around and keep my self bubbled and healed and Mind Sear when im not cursed. Same for second set. Once Anzu comes out of his Banish the second time I go for him even if birds are still up. One hell of a fight.", "date": "2010-10-20T18:57:37-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "When you're dotting up the adds as shadow, don't stand still! The chance for [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=78204]Shadowy Apparition[/url] to proc is increased greatly while you're moving, and the birds will drop much faster with that extra bit of damage.", "creationdate": "2010-10-21T18:06:44-05:00", "id": 461070, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1148752, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "aulm", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Instead of mind sear - try dropping out of shadow and using holy nova. AOE dmg to the adds and a self heal at the same time. Makes the fight much easier for shadow.", "creationdate": "2010-10-22T11:20:45-05:00", "id": 461141, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1148752, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "aggr1103", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-20T19:16:54-05:00", 2, "NeverFinal"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 112, "id": 1148789, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "148518", "body": "Running this as a shadow priest ilevel 264gear.\r\n\r\nEngage as normal, when he summons birds I throw single SWP dots on them and DP on one to help regen HP.  Watch his Spell Bomb (8 seconds) which causes casters to take damage when casting.\r\n\r\nBirds will die easily from a single dot.  Have dispersion ready if you get stunned and he starts beating on you.  Keep shield up.\r\n\r\nIf you are very low HP after a bird phase send in your Shadowfiend and hit Fade and let the minion tank while you pop some big heals on yourself.", "date": "2010-10-20T19:46:25-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Lol never thought to use Fiend and Fade. That will help. Hopefully the mount will drop quickly for me.", "creationdate": "2010-10-20T20:51:02-05:00", "id": 460996, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1148789, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "NeverFinal", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 113, "id": 1148954, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "356951", "body": "ummm...do you need to be attuned to enter level 70 heroics? \r\n\r\nwanna take other alts", "date": "2010-10-21T01:06:24-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Need honored with the affiliated faction to purchase the heroic key. In this case, Lower City.", "creationdate": "2010-10-21T14:09:06-05:00", "id": 187921, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1148954, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "VictoriouSecret", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Heroic keys have been taken out of the game with the keyring slot. You can now access Level 70 heroic dungeons without having to be Honored with their respective factions and the keys.", "creationdate": "2011-11-28T00:28:06-06:00", "id": 280458, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1148954, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Azunyan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 114, "id": 1149121, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Randomscrub", "body": "Solo'd as a arcane mage, keep the curse off and burn him as fast as you can. The adds did most of the damage to me. I got him to 3000 health before he used his second self banish pretty sure you can kill him before that if you get lucky.", "date": "2010-10-21T06:40:24-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 115, "id": 1149922, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "323155", "body": "The drop rate didn't increase at all, so I find the whining about this frustrating. Why should a specific class be necessary to get a dropped, not class specific mount? People that really wanted it just brought a Druid anyway.\r\n\r\nNot hard to solo as a 80 combat rogue in decent gear (I have mostly 264, some 277). Blow evasion at the beginning, get some space when he goes immune and bandage, pop blade flurry when the adds come down and use CPs on recuperate and keeping snd up - should be cake. I had full health when the 2nd swarm of adds died and I used no pots, no consumables other than bandages.", "date": "2010-10-22T00:56:03-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 116, "id": 1150859, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "662327", "body": "Having just done this as a Warlock in above average (3k wowheroes GS) gear, I learned patience is a virtue.\r\n\r\nI used a Voidwalker to tank and was in Affliction spec using Demon Armor for the healing benefit after getting my butt handed to me trying to blast him down as Destro.\r\n\r\nI sent in my VW and let him start building threat and threw a Curse of Weakness on Anzu firing off a Health Funnel when the VW got down to around 20k hp. When I saw Paralyzing Screech start to come up, I topped off the VW health before the stun. Once the threat got to a decent level I hit him with my DoT rotation.\r\n\r\nThe summoned adds were the real pain without the VW AoE taunt, so I just used Sacrifice and a Soulburned Seed of Corruption followed by a Shadowflame to DoT the adds unto death. Then it was just a matter of tabbing through the adds to make sure none were missed or using Rain of Fire if you still had the VW shield up so you didn't lose any damage to knockback.\r\n\r\nWhen Anzu comes out of his banish you'll have to hit him with Curse of Weakness again (it really helps) and basically start all over. Towards the end (after the second wave of adds) I used my Doomguard, but after the fight I wondered if I should have used my Infernal on one of the add waves. I may try that tomorrow.\r\n\r\nIts definitely a challenging fight for a Warlock, but can be done if you are patient and use all of the abilities you have at your disposal.\r\n\r\nOh, and after Anzu, go kill the last boss. There is no trash between Anzu and Ikiss and its so easy it isn't even funny, especially after Anzu.", "date": "2010-10-23T03:52:56-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I found it only doable with a Felguard. We don't have much by way of On-Demand AoE that doesn't hurt us.   Felstorm is perfect to destroy all those stupid birds without much problems.  If you don't have good Gear, the brewfest charms are good for both additional damage or healing while giving a nice tank-sized health pool  Remember to have a Healthstone on you, as well as Soul Link & Demon armor. Keep Curse of Weakness on Anzu", "creationdate": "2010-10-25T23:36:07-05:00", "id": 188728, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1150859, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "262083", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 117, "id": 1152309, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Narzul", "body": "Easy as BM hunter.\r\n\r\n1. Get a turtle with a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/petcalc#Mc0GhrMzbo0b]tanking spec[/url] (I put the point from Last Stand in Charge - not needed here).\r\n\r\n2. Get glyphs of Mending + Misdirection.\r\n\r\nKeep Misdirection + Mend Pet up. If you're lazy, call pet back + Feign Death when he becomes immune. Only one bird will attack you if you happen to be feigning death where it is programmed to go. If \\ when it's down, just wait until Anzu becomes active again.\r\n\r\nHappy hunting.", "date": "2010-10-24T18:09:46-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 118, "id": 1152456, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Tork64", "body": "Definitely doable as a disc priest, however he isn't as easy as people are making it out to be, his hits are devastating to a clothy, almost killed me, just make sure to have your shield/barrier up all the time, as for dps I just spammed smite and dots, the heals you get from atonement help. As he spawns the birds just spam holy nova, time everything. I did the instance with shadow up until Anzu, switched to disc then, just fyi.\n\n5.8 Shadow / 6.2 Disc", "date": "2010-10-24T23:40:38-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-24T23:44:22-05:00", 2, "Tork64"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 119, "id": 1152806, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "551048", "body": "You can easily do this as shadow if you have good gear.\n\n1. Pop shadowfiend.\n2. Fade.\n3. Nuke as much as possible pop trinkets etc.\n4. Kill birds with holy nova, use PoM and renew, use dispersion if you go under 50%.\n5. When adds are down, heal yourself up. \n\nAfter that it's easy.", "date": "2010-10-25T11:19:05-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-25T11:23:04-05:00", 1, "551048"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 120, "id": 1152819, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kabookiejoe", "body": "easily soloable as an elemental shaman\n\nburn him down, fast. when he summons adds drop a fire totem, flame nova plus earthquake or CL, whatever is your cup of tea. keep urself topped of with healing surge, especially when u see Paralyzing Screech begin to cast.  all in all, really quick fight, and pretty easy. and spell bombs is no longer a problem either, which is a plus", "date": "2010-10-25T11:38:56-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-10-29T10:43:47-05:00", 2, "kabookiejoe"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 121, "id": 1152972, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Jollef", "body": "[b]Anzu does not require any summon from a druid no more! \r\n\r\nF.y.i , thought you wanted to know :)[/b]", "date": "2010-10-25T15:14:58-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 122, "id": 1153701, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dragmarion", "body": "Piece of cake for fire mage with ICC gear.\r\n1)Nuke Anzu to 66%\r\n2)Kill adds (remember to remove curse ASAP)\r\n3)Pop Mirror Images and nuke Anzu to 33%.\r\n4)Kill adds (still with mirrors help).\r\n5)Finish boss.\r\n\r\nFeel free to use Iceblock/glyphed Evocation when you are in critical situation. Also recast Mana Shield everytime cd is off.\r\n\r\nThat's all.", "date": "2010-10-26T12:57:08-05:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 123, "id": 1163117, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kythil", "body": "Spell Bomb also stuns when you cast a spell while affect. Get that %^&* right.", "date": "2010-11-05T21:59:56-05:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=40303]Spell Bomb[/url] doesn't stun. It's a curse effect that damages you when you cast a spell while you're afflicted with it. It may look like a momentary stun, but it's only you taking damage.  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=40184]Paralyzing Screech[/url] is the one that stuns you for 6 seconds.", "creationdate": "2011-11-28T00:34:12-06:00", "id": 280461, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1163117, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Azunyan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
