{"commentv2": 1, "number": 125, "id": 1164519, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "694879", "body": "Since there hasn't been a posting yet, and this is one of my favorite mounts i figured that I would mention some changes as of 4.0.1.  Anzu no longer requires a druid to summon.  He is already in the room and the trash mobs that were once there are now gone!  I just checked it out today on my mage and was able to solo him thanks to glyphed evocation.  I don't PVE on my mage, but I am in full wrathful PVP gear, and Anzu still gave me a good run.  Sadly the mount didn't drop so I tried an bug I used in Heroic Escape from Durnholde Keep to reset the instance.  Unfortunately, it looks like you are only able to enter here once a day so it will still be a bit of a grind if you're looking for the mount.\r\n\r\nGood luck and happy hunting!", "date": "2010-11-07T12:30:55-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 126, "id": 1165193, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "118944", "body": "Solo'd as an arcane mage in 4.0.1.  Took a couple of attempts to figure out, but then it's not so hard.  Mana shield, you can pretty much stand and burn him to the phase changes.  Aoe most of the birds, you can slow/kite one if you need time to regen cooldowns.  End the birds phase on the opposite side of the room from Anzu so you have time to glyphed evoc or bandage if needed.  You can use mirrors if needed, but be aware that if you do he may cast the cyclone on you - be ready to interrupt it.", "date": "2010-11-08T06:58:58-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "soloed as an arcane mage also. plan i used was: popped mana shield at start and full dpsed with cooldowns until the bird phase. then i spammed arcane explosion until all birds were down. after that i popped mirror immages to keep aggro off me while i was casting evocation to heal myself. after that i continued to fully dps him until he was down. i equipped a medallion of the horde because i did not know that i could interrupt the stuns. he casted only 2 until i killed him so stuns were not a problem.", "creationdate": "2010-11-08T16:15:55-06:00", "id": 191180, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1165193, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mustardeetee", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 127, "id": 1165347, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "virulence", "body": "I went into Sethekk Halls today to give it another go at this mount but Anzu was nowhere to be seen and all the normal trash had spawned inside the room. Anyone know what's going down with that?", "date": "2010-11-08T10:51:40-06:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "are you sure you were in heroic mode?", "creationdate": "2010-11-08T18:46:25-06:00", "id": 191197, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1165347, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "shortleif", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 128, "id": 1167477, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "700004", "body": "I soloed this boss today for the first time on my shadow priest. It took me about four tries to get it, but, I found that the way to do this was to DoT the boss the first time around and use Mind Flay.\r\n\r\nIt's important to pay attention to when he starts summoning the all the owls because you want to apply Shadow Word: Pain on as many of them as you can before they begin to attack. Otherwise, you get stun-locked by them kicking you in the face, and no one wants that. Then make sure you have your shield up and they should die pretty quickly for the most part.\r\n\r\nAfter that, I just had to DoT the boss and kite him around; didn't really bother much with Mind Flay. Rinse and repeat. :@", "date": "2010-11-10T16:41:05-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 129, "id": 1168764, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shirlnha", "body": "Just soloed this as a Balance Druid. I stayed in caster form so I could heal myself, and the spirits. Between healing myself and the bird spirits I threw a Starsurge and some Moonfires and Insect Swarms and Typhoons (basically any instant-cast damage spell I had at my disposal) at Anzu. Took me like 3 minutes. Sadly, no mount.", "date": "2010-11-12T05:13:22-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-11-12T05:13:59-06:00", 1, "Shirlnha"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 130, "id": 1177580, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "283705", "body": "Easily soloed by an Elemental Shaman. Given, I'm decked out in average 266, but Anzu doesnt hit hard at all, only some trash mobs are somewhat a threat.", "date": "2010-11-22T09:28:42-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 131, "id": 1192756, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dramoner", "body": "Was Farming him today for Reins of the Raven Lord, and in about the middle of the fight he whispered:- ''your magic shall be your undoing... ak-a-ak'' ...strangest thing ever.\n\nEDIT: and this time:- ''Yes... cast your precious little spells, ak-a-ak!''", "date": "2010-11-28T08:21:16-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "He does this emote several times in every fight.  It means he just put a debuff on you that will drain some of your mana and do damage to you if you cast a spell.  Only auto attacks and melee attacks will not count against you.", "creationdate": "2010-11-29T20:40:11-06:00", "id": 197031, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1192756, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Unpossible", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Aaah, kk thx! That explains it then :P", "creationdate": "2014-11-13T08:47:16-06:00", "id": 788649, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1192756, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dramoner", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-12-05T08:23:55-06:00", 2, "Dramoner"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 132, "id": 1196769, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "giggins", "body": "Solo'd him as a frost mage. Without too much trouble, wearing a mix of icc 10/25 gear.\n\n1. Place your water elemental in front of Anzu.\n2. Run to the side of Anzu, hugging the wall.\n3. Let the water elemental pull with a frostbolt.\n4. Run behind Anzu, by then the elemental should have a decent amount of threat.\n5. Use your water element's frost nova (to proc fingers of frost).\n6. Shoot off a frostbolt, followed by a deep freeze. If fingers of frost is stacked twice then shoot off an ice lance. If not use a cone of cold and kite him around.\n7. Hopefully, by now Anzu is in phase 2.\n8. Refresh ice barrier and get some distance between you and Anzu.\n9. Once you come out of the stun, use frost nova and blink.\n10. Use blizzard to AoE the birds down. If necessary, ice block, use your water element's frost nova and blink. Don't be afraid to let the birds hit you, ice barrier will hold up if glyph'd.\n11. Once Anzu becomes live again, use invisibility and let your elemental regain threat. Cancel invisibility after 3-5 seconds. \n12. Pop mirrors and icy veins, also your water element's frost nova to proc fingers of frost, then use deep freeze.\n13. If your lucky you'll have Anzu down before another phase. If not repeat 8-10.\n14. After AoE'ing the birds (assuming you had another phase) your fingers of frost should be proc'd, use a deep freeze and an ice lance if necessary to finish him off.\n16. Cross your fingers and collect the loot.\n\nNote: Remember to keep ice barrier up at all time if possible. You may wanna bring a heath potion and if your a Draenei, Gift of the Naaru helps too.", "date": "2010-11-29T23:48:20-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-11-29T23:52:54-06:00", 2, "giggins"]}
