{"commentv2": 1, "number": 134, "id": 1203898, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "131549", "body": "Possible to solo as a Mutilate Rogue in 264 (average) gear.\r\n\r\nStrategy:  \r\n\r\nKill two guards just outside entrance to Anzu.  As second one is about to go down, hit Recuperate (hopefully with 5 combo points)\r\n\r\nStealth, run in, frontal attack to generate more combo points.  Hit rupture as soon as you hit 5 combo points.  I do not pop Evasion during Phase 1, but you might want to, depends on your toon's stats...\r\n\r\nUse normal rotation, but make sure you have 5 combo points built up just before Anzu hits 66%.  Hit Recuperate and back off a bit.\r\n\r\nWhile birds are swarming, you should be able to heal for quite a bit, then FoK and burn them down.  Attack Anzu again, hit Rupture at 5 combo points, and hopefully Recuperate with 5 combo points just before he hits 33%.\r\n\r\nBack off as before, use a bandage and consider a healing Pot if your health warrants it.  When birds swarm this time, you may have to pop Evasion, burn again with FoK.\r\n\r\nAttack immediately when Phase 3 starts.  If Anzu's health is low enough, burn him...if a bit too high, use Rupture at 5 combo points and continue to burn.  Use Cloak of Shadows if you need to mitigate some damage.  Burn down and (hopefully), you kill the boss.\r\n\r\nUsing this strategy, I usually have at least 25% health remaining, highest has been 57%.\r\n\r\nGood luck!", "date": "2010-12-03T10:08:24-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Possible? Yes. I've been soloing Anzu since the patch that made him permanently available without a druid to summon as a mut rogue easily.  No need to kill the guards, just distract them and stealth past. When you engage Anzu, they will not come in after you.  Make sure you're stealthed and auto attack the boss to engage him. Hit your Vendetta and once you get to 5 CPs use Recuperate. 4-5 more CP use Envenom and build up more CPs, make sure to keep some spare CPs up during his banish so you can easily refresh Recup. By now he should be around 60% and he'll go immune. So bandage yourself up and", "creationdate": "2010-12-03T10:08:25-06:00", "id": 465885, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1203898, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Melodieous", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I suggested killing the guards so that Recuperate would be up when you engage Anzu...every little bit helps! :)", "creationdate": "2010-12-11T05:45:14-06:00", "id": 201941, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1203898, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "131549", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-12-03T20:29:45-06:00", 1, "131549"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 135, "id": 1238965, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "254283", "body": "As a tip to combat rogues: It's easy to get him once you use recuperate. Don't pull any other guards or anything. Just stay on Anzu and use Recuperate and all your other abilities. Don't need no potions or anything.", "date": "2010-12-16T18:04:02-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
