{"commentv2": 1, "number": 145, "id": 1328948, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "DELsh1van", "body": "upon entering Sethekk Halls heroic to solo anzu today after the patch hit, I found the SH normal mobs in the room with Anzu nowhere to be found. Dungeon difficulty was definitely on heroic upon entering.\r\n\r\nany clue? any chance this is a patch bug?", "date": "2011-02-09T16:02:00-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Same thing happened to me today, and the instance was without a doubt on heroic.  Pretty %^&*ty to have a wasted mount run day.", "creationdate": "2011-04-22T07:41:30-05:00", "id": 239038, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1328948, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "615466", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I had this happen to me today, but I figured out the issue. Even though I had selected \"heroic\" and it showed the heroic skull at the portal, upon zoning in it wasn't actually a heroic instance. I zoned out after clearing the place, changed it to \"normal\" then back to heroic and it was indeed heroic this time. You can tell because on a true heroic you will get the message saying you're saved to the instance once you kill a boss. Pity I didn't realize this when I cleared Magister's Terrace on \"heroic\" before SK =_=", "creationdate": "2011-12-17T21:31:18-06:00", "id": 498421, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1328948, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Aknazer", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@Aknazer I can confirm this works. thanks so much", "creationdate": "2012-05-22T20:28:53-05:00", "id": 545316, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1328948, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "422047", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 146, "id": 1332513, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "shinazueli", "body": "He's still there as of 18:53 server 2/11/2011.", "date": "2011-02-11T22:53:35-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Also confirming that he's still there. I went in for the first time since the change to make druids no longer required to summon him and got lucky enough to get the mount too.", "creationdate": "2011-02-17T01:50:49-06:00", "id": 478836, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1332513, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "256772", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 147, "id": 1339333, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "xonsuns", "body": "Still there day after day in 4.0.6.. and still droping crap items but the mount. In two times i get a loot bug (grey bag although over the body) but nothing to worry about.\r\n\r\nbalance druid-> stealth through the boss: Hit strong 'till banish, wait 3 seg put thorns on you and hurricane in your position... kill adds and get back on boss. Sometimes you get an annoying Paralyzing Screech but nothing to worry about.", "date": "2011-02-17T03:32:47-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Some other general tips for Balance Druids:  - [b]Cast Rejuvenation on the Hawk spirit AND on yourself when he banishes.[/b] A little damage mitigation goes a long way when he suddenly hits you with a Paralyzing Screech and you're not geared enough. - [b]Always keep Thorns active.[/b] Mighty helpful when you can't do jack while stunned. - [b]Wild Mushrooms over Hurricane.[/b] Drop them before you start the fight, and they will instant kill those annoying adds (provided you have Thorns active). Hurricane needs to be channeled and takes a huge chunk of mana. Definitely not helpful when you keep ", "creationdate": "2011-02-17T03:32:48-06:00", "id": 481965, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1339333, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Azunyan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 148, "id": 1350909, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "587126", "body": "I went to the duengon and I din't find him there, so do you still have to have a druid that can summon him? The room that WoWHead says he is in is just full of trash...", "date": "2011-02-26T13:51:46-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The room being full of trash might mean that your dungeon difficulty was set to regular. Anzu spawns only in heroic mode. In reg mode you will find the room overcrowded with those annoying fear casting guys that always used to be there.  No, no druid required. You can go solo on any class toon, or (if you are at the right level) with a dungeon finder pug. Just remember: heroic mode or no Anzu. :)", "creationdate": "2011-02-27T20:32:11-06:00", "id": 228848, "rating": 6, "commentid": 1350909, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "662504", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 149, "id": 1372768, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "404619", "body": "Being him a raven and so, wouldn't it be nice if he were a flying mount now?", "date": "2011-03-21T15:19:56-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "He did serve as part of the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/quest=11001/vanquish-the-raven-god]quest[/url] for the Druid [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=40120]Swift Flight Form[/url] though. I do kinda wonder if the fourth [url=http://www.wowhead.com/quest=10607]\"Prophecy of the Raven God\"[/url] meant Anzu not being able to fly anymore.", "creationdate": "2011-03-22T10:50:25-05:00", "id": 233750, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1372768, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Azunyan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "There was the Dread Raven from WoD Collector's Edition, but you can no longer get it", "creationdate": "2017-08-27T00:34:13-05:00", "id": 1068654, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1372768, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Matsen115", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 150, "id": 1375408, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Athenia", "body": "Soloed as 83 Arcane mage. Only got fairly crappy gear with some pieces of T10, so only kicking around 57k HP.\n\nStart at absolute max range and nuke with Arcane Blast, hopefully by the time he gets to you he will be about ready to banish and bring out the adds.\nWatch for his 8 second stun and hit ice block just before it lands, you'll still get stunned but as you're ice blocked the adds won't be able to hit you.\nOnce the stun wears off, drop ice block, nova, blink, and blizzard or spam flamestrike to kill the adds.\n\nWhen the adds are dead pop mirror image and nuke him until he banishes again.\n\nNext set of adds, pop mana shield and wait for the stun again - this time nova the adds and blink just before it lands, this will buy you some time for the adds to not be wailing on you. Again, once it wears off finish the adds and him.\n\n[b]Be aware of the curse he puts on you, if you cast with it on it will hit you much harder than either the boss or the adds do. Make a macro and mash it as soon as you see the curse land.[/b]\n\nGood luck farming the mount!\n\nEdit: If you're unsure about taking him down in one shot, go into the next room past Anzu and kill Ikiss - he's very easy and doing so will open up the back door so you can get back to Anzu more quickly if/when he kills you.", "date": "2011-03-25T01:13:33-05:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-03-25T01:18:18-05:00", 1, "Athenia"]}
