{"commentv2": 1, "number": 181, "id": 1656477, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Terakahn", "body": "While I've killed the boss before solo, I'm curious about something.\n\nWent to do a mount run today, and for some reason he's not there. \nIt's been about a week since I killed him last, and he's missing this time.\n\nAny ideas or explanations why this happened?\n\nEdit: Figured it out. It was set to heroic, but the instance wasn't actually heroic. Double check mob level before you start clearing the place. There's a good chance you just need to leave, and reset the difficulty. I put it to regular and then heroic again and reset all instances. Worked like a charm.", "date": "2012-04-20T10:53:19-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "He wasn't there when i went in tonight, either. There was a skull when i went in so i was a little confused. It seems ridiculous to have to switch to normal and then back to heroic. /: But this fix did work for me.", "creationdate": "2012-04-22T04:07:54-05:00", "id": 537704, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1656477, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "luinel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-04-20T11:09:40-05:00", 1, "Terakahn"]}
